[{"question":"Are you under the influence of any substances?","answer":"No.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":3,"aSentId":4},{"question":"When you watch what\u0027s happening with Charlie right now, what are you thinking?","answer":"P.T. Barnum.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":32,"aSentId":33},{"question":"Do you accept any of that?","answer":"I think maybe the whole machete thing might have been something that he\u0027s running and gunning with right now but certainly the home tape that he did the night before, I fully recognized and I heard a clip that you had, I think it was Todd Bridges who made the comment of, yes, I\u0027ve been there, I know that -- I know that guy.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":40,"aSentId":41},{"question":"I mean are you seriously worried that Charlie Sheen is slowly killing himself here?","answer":"Yes, I don\u0027t even think it\u0027s slowly right now.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":44,"aSentId":45},{"question":"I mean the man has an anger issue, a rage issue, and I think the more that people like you who have this incredible platform to come from who are -- I don\u0027t want to use the word enabling but who are sort of egging him on, tickling that little funny bone that says, yes, yes, this is -- hey, I\u0027ve got, you know, Aunt Donna\u0027s DNA and I feel like people love to watch a circus, right?","answer":"I mean I\u0027m told --","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":88,"aSentId":89},{"question":"I mean when you hear him talk like that, what are you seeing, the classic signs of an addict in your view?","answer":"Oh, without question.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":122,"aSentId":123},{"question":"And being the face of CBS which is, you know, supposed to be a family, you know, network and the families out there, and he\u0027s working with a 9 or 10 or 11-year-old boy, so he comes into the set, he\u0027s off a crack run, he\u0027s been with a few hookers the night before, what do you think he\u0027s talking about with an 11-year-old?","answer":"Well, look, he --","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":149,"aSentId":150},{"question":"What was it that finally snapped you back into normal life again?","answer":"I don\u0027t think I had ever been afraid of the drug itself before.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":185,"aSentId":186},{"question":"And Mackenzie, for you, was it -- Mackenzie, for you, was it getting fired from the show that finally woke you up?","answer":"No.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":192,"aSentId":193},{"question":"Or does he have to save himself?","answer":"I think it\u0027s got to be a combination of both.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":209,"aSentId":210},{"question":"I mean if Charlie used to go down this road how difficult is it?","answer":"It won\u0027t be easy for him as the doctor just mentioned.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":234,"aSentId":235},{"question":"Am I right, Dr. Samuels?","answer":"Right.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":248,"aSentId":249},{"question":"Do you think he really has any concept of what\u0027s going on here?","answer":"To be honest with you I couldn\u0027t answer that question.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":289,"aSentId":290},{"question":"What kind of people were your parents?","answer":"They were very nice people.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":301,"aSentId":302},{"question":"Was there any stress or trouble that you could look at and say well, maybe we should have seen warning signs here?","answer":"Absolutely none.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":310,"aSentId":311},{"question":"When did you hear what had happened?","answer":"Probably 20 minutes after it had happened.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":315,"aSentId":316},{"question":"What-- how do you possibly come to terms with it?","answer":"It is just absolute disbelief.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":322,"aSentId":323},{"question":"Do you know where he got the guns?","answer":"No idea.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":327,"aSentId":328},{"question":"I mean, what do you think will happen next for this family?","answer":"You know, we will just continue to pull together like we had this last week and take care of one another.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":335,"aSentId":336},{"question":"Did you get any kind of inkling that something like this could ever happen?","answer":"No, I never saw anything like this.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":340,"aSentId":341},{"question":"Do you think that is the correct way this should proceed?","answer":"That\u0027s a hard question for me to answer.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":350,"aSentId":351},{"question":"What can you possibly say to them?","answer":"Man, I don\u0027t know.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":360,"aSentId":361},{"question":"Was she right to go?","answer":"Well, first, let me explain that as the ombudsman of NPR, I am not representing NPR.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":400,"aSentId":401},{"question":"Can you be responsible if you are chief executive of such a huge organization for everything that everybody in it does and says?","answer":"Well, as I understand, the board basically decided that there have been too many things that have happened recently that would make it -- that hindered Vivian Schiller from actually going ahead and doing her job.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":411,"aSentId":412},{"question":"Would it be easier if the NPR simply wasn\u0027t funded by the government?","answer":"Well, certainly not right off the bat.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":417,"aSentId":418},{"question":"Is this kind of stunt fair game, do you think?","answer":"Well, of course, it\u0027s fair game.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":426,"aSentId":427},{"question":"This guy wouldn\u0027t have said this stuff if he knew he was being recorded, would he?","answer":"No, but this is done all the time.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":442,"aSentId":443},{"question":"Well, you are, really, aren\u0027t you?","answer":"No more so than Geraldo Rivera -- than Geraldo Rivera is.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":454,"aSentId":455},{"question":"Where do you draw the line?","answer":"If James O\u0027Keefe, who is an independent journalist, comes to me with something that doesn\u0027t sit right with me, I\u0027m going to pass on it.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":467,"aSentId":468},{"question":"How do you ensure that somebody else isn\u0027t right now getting stitched up?","answer":"Well, I think that it\u0027s a cautionary tale, that this is a new world we live in.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":476,"aSentId":477},{"question":"Andrew?","answer":"Well, first of all, I will say this: the best coverage on this incident has been NPR.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":485,"aSentId":486},{"question":"They\u0027re not all choir boys, are they?","answer":"I could accept that.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":494,"aSentId":495},{"question":"How did you manage to avoid the terrible fate that befell your colleagues?","answer":"Because I woke up one day, 27 years old -- I remember it was my last court appearance.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":537,"aSentId":538},{"question":"What was rock bottom?","answer":"Rock bottom for me was one day I was at a motel.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":572,"aSentId":573},{"question":"When did you hear that Gary had died?","answer":"I was actually out at Lake San Antonio on my jet skis.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":591,"aSentId":592},{"question":"Right?","answer":"That\u0027s exactly right.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":615,"aSentId":616},{"question":"Arnold, ain\u0027t I your big brother who loves you, who worries about you?","answer":"And takes care of you, yes.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":631,"aSentId":632},{"question":"Todd, when you see what\u0027s happened to Charlie Sheen, what goes through your mind?","answer":"Well, for me, I know that addiction is very powerful.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":635,"aSentId":636},{"question":"Why do people do that?","answer":"Because for me, I think what I was going through -- I call it cocaine psychosis.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":646,"aSentId":647},{"question":"Do you worry what will happen to Charlie if he doesn\u0027t get help?","answer":"Yeah, everyone -- anybody who is in addiction, you know what -- there\u0027s three things that can happen, end up mentally crazy the rest of your life, in prison the rest of your life or you\u0027re going to die.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":657,"aSentId":658},{"question":"Have you met Charlie Sheen?","answer":"I know him.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":661,"aSentId":662},{"question":"If you got a chance to talk to him, what would you say to him?","answer":"A lot of things, but I would try to figure out the core of his problem.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":679,"aSentId":680},{"question":"Do you think it was a mistake to get rid of Paula?","answer":"Certainly, yeah.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":720,"aSentId":721},{"question":"What do you think of Steven Tyler and J-Lo?","answer":"Good.","docId":"110309pmt","qSentId":727,"aSentId":728}]